{"type":"message","id":"1ac0bc6d","parentId":"899c10db","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:16:38.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ayw2av0syyvq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 121430\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. CFI Analysis was completed (Phase 1 Advancement) - found that 44.8% of invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise), only 5.7% have high CFI\r\n3. Key pending items include:\r\n   - CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n   - Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n   - Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n   - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n   - Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe CFI analysis results suggest a clear next step: implement CFI-weighted compression. This would filter out the noise (CFI=0) and focus on the true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7).\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete file edit would advance this goal. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a compression experiment that:\r\n   - Takes the current frequency-based invariants\r\n   - Applies CFI weighting\r\n   - Compares prediction quality\r\n\r\nSince the last pulse noted \"No mutations applied this cycle\", I need to make progress. The natural next action is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new document or script that implements this experiment. The most concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create a compression experiment script or document that uses CFI weights\r\n2. Or update the CFI_RESULTS.md with experimental protocol\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, I should create a new file or modify an existing one to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. Let me create a simple experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the frequency analysis data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting\r\n3. Compares against frequency baseline\r\n\r\nOr I could create a new document outlining the experiment design.\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction, I'll create a new experiment script or update a research document. Let me create a compression experiment that builds on the CFI analysis.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll develop a script that quantifies the CFI filtering's impact on compression efficiency and prediction accuracy.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The logical next step is to implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether filtering by CFI improves next-pulse prediction quality compared to the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a new experiment script `research/cfi_compression_experiment.py` that implements CFI-weighted compression and compares prediction quality against frequency-only baseline. This directly addresses the pending \"CFI-weighted compression experiment\" task.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n# Compares CFI-filtered compression vs frequency-only baseline\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\n# Load frequency analysis results\r\nfreq_file = Path(\"research/frequency_analysis.json\")\r\nif freq_file.exists():\r\n    with open(freq_file) as f:\r\n        freq_data = json.load(f)\r\n\r\n# Load CFI results  \r\ncfi_file = Path(\"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\")\r\nif not cfi_file.exists():\r\n    print(\"CFI_RESULTS.md not found - run CFI analysis first\")\r\n    exit(1)\r\n\r\n# Parse CFI findings from the report\r\n# Key metrics from prior analysis:\r\n# - 44.8% of invariants: CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming)\r\n# - 5.7% of invariants: CFI>=0.7 (true causal anchors)  \r\n# - Mean CFI: 0.181\r\n\r\nclass CFIPredictor:\r\n    \"\"\"Compression using CFI weights instead of raw frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, invariants, cfi_scores, threshold=0.7):\r\n        self.invariants = invariants\r\n        self.cfi_scores = cfi_scores  # dict: invariant -> CFI score\r\n        self.threshold = threshold\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current_state):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict next pulse content using CFI-weighted scoring.\"\"\"\r\n        candidates = []\r\n        for inv in self.invariants:\r\n            cfi = self.cfi_scores.get(inv, 0)\r\n            freq = self.invariants[inv][\"frequency\"]\r\n            # CFI-weighted score: prioritize high-CFI invariants\r\n            score = cfi * freq if cfi >= self.threshold else 0\r\n            if score > 0:\r\n                candidates.append((inv, score))\r\n        \r\n        candidates.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\r\n        return [c[0] for c in candidates[:10]]\r\n    \r\n    def compression_ratio(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Calculate compression ratio with CFI filtering.\"\"\"\r\n        total = len(self.invariants)\r\n        retained = sum(1 for inv in self.invariants \r\n                      if self.cfi_scores.get(inv, 0) >= self.threshold)\r\n        return retained / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n\r\nclass FrequencyBaseline:\r\n    \"\"\"Baseline: pure frequency-based compression.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, invariants):\r\n        self.invariants = invariants\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current_state):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict using frequency rank only.\"\"\"\r\n        sorted_inv = sorted(self.invariants.items(), \r\n                           key=lambda x: x[1][\"frequency\"], \r\n                           reverse=True)\r\n        return [inv for inv, _ in sorted_inv[:10]]\r\n    \r\n    def compression_ratio(self):\r\n        return 1.0  # Baseline retains all invariants\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Compare CFI-weighted vs frequency baseline on prediction accuracy.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"CFI-WEIGHTED\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:14:55\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368998061}}
